{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I grew up in Europe, and World War II caught me"},{"time":5000,"text":"when I was between seven and 10 years old."},{"time":9000,"text":"And I realized how few of the grown-ups that I knew"},{"time":16000,"text":"were able to withstand the tragedies that the war visited on them --"},{"time":26000,"text":"how few of them could even resemble a normal, contented,"},{"time":34000,"text":"satisfied, happy life once their job, their home, their security"},{"time":43000,"text":"was destroyed by the war."},{"time":45000,"text":"So I became interested in understanding"},{"time":48000,"text":"what contributed to a life that was worth living."},{"time":53000,"text":"And I tried, as a child, as a teenager, to read philosophy"},{"time":59000,"text":"and to get involved in art and religion and many other ways"},{"time":67000,"text":"that I could see as a possible answer to that question."},{"time":71000,"text":"And finally I ended up encountering psychology by chance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80000,"text":"I was at a ski resort in Switzerland without any money"},{"time":85000,"text":"to actually enjoy myself, because the snow had melted and"},{"time":93000,"text":"I didn't have money to go to a movie. But I found that on the --"},{"time":98000,"text":"I read in the newspapers that there was to be a presentation"},{"time":103000,"text":"by someone in a place that I'd seen in the center of Zurich,"},{"time":109000,"text":"and it was about flying saucers [that] he was going to talk."},{"time":115000,"text":"And I thought, well, since I can't go to the movies,"},{"time":117000,"text":"at least I will go for free to listen to flying saucers."},{"time":123000,"text":"And the man who talked at that evening lecture was very interesting."},{"time":132000,"text":"Instead of talking about little green men,"},{"time":135000,"text":"he talked about how the psyche of the Europeans"},{"time":140000,"text":"had been traumatized by the war, and now they're projecting"},{"time":144000,"text":"flying saucers into the sky."},{"time":148000,"text":"He talked about how the mandalas of ancient Hindu religion"},{"time":153000,"text":"were kind of projected into the sky as an attempt to regain"},{"time":160000,"text":"some sense of order after the chaos of war."},{"time":164000,"text":"And this seemed very interesting to me."},{"time":167000,"text":"And I started reading his books after that lecture."},{"time":170000,"text":"And that was Carl Jung, whose name or work I had no idea about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178000,"text":"Then I came to this country to study psychology"},{"time":181000,"text":"and I started trying to understand the roots of happiness."},{"time":188000,"text":"This is a typical result that many people have presented,"},{"time":193000,"text":"and there are many variations on it."},{"time":196000,"text":"But this, for instance, shows that about 30 percent of the people"},{"time":200000,"text":"surveyed in the United States since 1956"},{"time":204000,"text":"say that their life is very happy."},{"time":208000,"text":"And that hasn't changed at all."},{"time":210000,"text":"Whereas the personal income,"},{"time":212000,"text":"on a scale that has been held constant to accommodate for inflation,"},{"time":218000,"text":"has more than doubled, almost tripled, in that period."},{"time":222000,"text":"But you find essentially the same results,"},{"time":226000,"text":"namely, that after a certain basic point -- which corresponds more or less"},{"time":231000,"text":"to just a few 1,000 dollars above the minimum poverty level --"},{"time":235000,"text":"increases in material well-being don't seem to affect how happy people are."},{"time":242000,"text":"In fact, you can find that the lack of basic resources,"},{"time":249000,"text":"material resources, contributes to unhappiness,"},{"time":252000,"text":"but the increase in material resources does not increase happiness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"So my research has been focused more on --"},{"time":263000,"text":"after finding out these things that actually corresponded"},{"time":270000,"text":"to my own experience, I tried to understand:"},{"time":273000,"text":"where -- in everyday life, in our normal experience --"},{"time":279000,"text":"do we feel really happy?"},{"time":282000,"text":"And to start"},{"time":286000,"text":"those studies about 40 years ago, I began to look at creative people --"},{"time":291000,"text":"first artists and scientists, and so forth -- trying to understand"},{"time":297000,"text":"what made them feel that it was worth essentially spending their life"},{"time":307000,"text":"doing things for which many of them didn't expect either fame or fortune,"},{"time":313000,"text":"but which made their life meaningful and worth doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318000,"text":"This was one of the leading composers of American music back in the '70s."},{"time":324000,"text":"And the interview was 40 pages long."},{"time":327000,"text":"But this little excerpt is a very good summary"},{"time":331000,"text":"of what he was saying during the interview."},{"time":335000,"text":"And it describes how he feels when composing is going well."},{"time":340000,"text":"And he says by describing it as an ecstatic state."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344000,"text":"Now, \"ecstasy\" in Greek meant"},{"time":346000,"text":"simply to stand to the side of something."},{"time":349000,"text":"And then it became essentially an analogy for a mental state"},{"time":356000,"text":"where you feel that you are not doing your ordinary everyday routines."},{"time":362000,"text":"So ecstasy is essentially a stepping into an alternative reality."},{"time":368000,"text":"And it's interesting, if you think about it, how, when we think about"},{"time":373000,"text":"the civilizations that we look up to as having been pinnacles of human achievement --"},{"time":379000,"text":"whether it's China, Greece, the Hindu civilization,"},{"time":384000,"text":"or the Mayas, or Egyptians -- what we know about them"},{"time":389000,"text":"is really about their ecstasies, not about their everyday life."},{"time":394000,"text":"We know the temples they built, where people could come"},{"time":397000,"text":"to experience a different reality."},{"time":399000,"text":"We know about the circuses,"},{"time":402000,"text":"the arenas, the theaters."},{"time":405000,"text":"These are the remains of civilizations and they are the places that people went"},{"time":413000,"text":"to experience life in a more concentrated, more ordered form."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422000,"text":"Now, this man doesn't need to go to a place like this,"},{"time":426000,"text":"which is also -- this place, this arena, which is built"},{"time":430000,"text":"like a Greek amphitheatre, is a place for ecstasy also."},{"time":434000,"text":"We are participating in a reality that is different"},{"time":438000,"text":"from that of the everyday life that we're used to."},{"time":441000,"text":"But this man doesn't need to go there."},{"time":444000,"text":"He needs just a piece of paper where he can put down little marks,"},{"time":450000,"text":"and as he does that, he can imagine sounds"},{"time":456000,"text":"that had not existed before in that particular combination."},{"time":460000,"text":"So once he gets to that point of beginning to create,"},{"time":466000,"text":"like Jennifer did in her improvisation,"},{"time":469000,"text":"a new reality -- that is, a moment of ecstasy --"},{"time":474000,"text":"he enters that different reality."},{"time":477000,"text":"Now he says also that this is so intense an experience"},{"time":481000,"text":"that it feels almost as if he didn't exist."},{"time":484000,"text":"And that sounds like a kind of a romantic exaggeration."},{"time":490000,"text":"But actually, our nervous system is incapable of processing"},{"time":494000,"text":"more than about 110 bits of information per second."},{"time":499000,"text":"And in order to hear me and understand what I'm saying,"},{"time":503000,"text":"you need to process about 60 bits per second."},{"time":507000,"text":"That's why you can't hear more than two people."},{"time":510000,"text":"You can't understand more than two people talking to you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513000,"text":"Well, when you are really involved in this completely engaging process"},{"time":524000,"text":"of creating something new, as this man is,"},{"time":527000,"text":"he doesn't have enough attention left over to monitor"},{"time":533000,"text":"how his body feels, or his problems at home."},{"time":537000,"text":"He can't feel even that he's hungry or tired."},{"time":540000,"text":"His body disappears,"},{"time":543000,"text":"his identity disappears from his consciousness,"},{"time":548000,"text":"because he doesn't have enough attention, like none of us do,"},{"time":552000,"text":"to really do well something that requires a lot of concentration,"},{"time":558000,"text":"and at the same time to feel that he exists."},{"time":560000,"text":"So existence is temporarily suspended."},{"time":565000,"text":"And he says that his hand seems to be moving by itself."},{"time":571000,"text":"Now, I could look at my hand for two weeks, and I wouldn't feel"},{"time":579000,"text":"any awe or wonder, because I can't compose. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":583000,"text":"So what it's telling you here"},{"time":585000,"text":"is that obviously this automatic,"},{"time":592000,"text":"spontaneous process that he's describing can only happen to someone"},{"time":597000,"text":"who is very well trained and who has developed technique."},{"time":601000,"text":"And it has become a kind of a truism in the study of creativity"},{"time":608000,"text":"that you can't be creating anything with less than 10 years"},{"time":613000,"text":"of technical-knowledge immersion in a particular field."},{"time":619000,"text":"Whether it's mathematics or music, it takes that long"},{"time":624000,"text":"to be able to begin to change something in a way that it's better"},{"time":632000,"text":"than what was there before."},{"time":635000,"text":"Now, when that happens,"},{"time":637000,"text":"he says the music just flows out."},{"time":639000,"text":"And because all of these people I started interviewing --"},{"time":643000,"text":"this was an interview which is over 30 years old --"},{"time":649000,"text":"so many of the people described this as a spontaneous flow"},{"time":653000,"text":"that I called this type of experience the \"flow experience.\""},{"time":658000,"text":"And it happens in different realms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661000,"text":"For instance, a poet describes it in this form."},{"time":665000,"text":"This is by a student of mine who interviewed"},{"time":668000,"text":"some of the leading writers and poets in the United States."},{"time":671000,"text":"And it describes the same effortless, spontaneous feeling"},{"time":677000,"text":"that you get when you enter into this ecstatic state."},{"time":680000,"text":"This poet describes it as opening a door that floats in the sky --"},{"time":685000,"text":"a very similar description to what Albert Einstein gave"},{"time":688000,"text":"as to how he imagined the forces of relativity,"},{"time":694000,"text":"when he was struggling with trying to understand how it worked."},{"time":698000,"text":"But it happens in other activities."},{"time":703000,"text":"For instance, this is another student of mine,"},{"time":705000,"text":"Susan Jackson from Australia, who did work"},{"time":709000,"text":"with some of the leading athletes in the world."},{"time":713000,"text":"And you see here in this description of an Olympic skater,"},{"time":717000,"text":"the same essential description of the phenomenology"},{"time":720000,"text":"of the inner state of the person."},{"time":722000,"text":"You don't think; it goes automatically,"},{"time":725000,"text":"if you merge yourself with the music, and so forth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729000,"text":"It happens also, actually, in the most recent book I wrote,"},{"time":733000,"text":"called \"Good Business,\" where I interviewed some of the CEOs"},{"time":736000,"text":"who had been nominated by their peers as being both very successful"},{"time":741000,"text":"and very ethical, very socially responsible."},{"time":744000,"text":"You see that these people define success"},{"time":748000,"text":"as something that helps others and at the same time"},{"time":753000,"text":"makes you feel happy as you are working at it."},{"time":756000,"text":"And like all of these successful and responsible CEOs say,"},{"time":763000,"text":"you can't have just one of these things be successful"},{"time":770000,"text":"if you want a meaningful and successful job."},{"time":773000,"text":"Anita Roddick is another one of these CEOs we interviewed."},{"time":778000,"text":"She is the founder of Body Shop,"},{"time":782000,"text":"the natural cosmetics king."},{"time":784000,"text":"It's kind of a passion that comes"},{"time":786000,"text":"from doing the best and having flow while you're working."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790000,"text":"This is an interesting little quote from Masaru Ibuka,"},{"time":794000,"text":"who was at that time starting out Sony without any money,"},{"time":799000,"text":"without a product -- they didn't have a product,"},{"time":801000,"text":"they didn't have anything, but they had an idea."},{"time":804000,"text":"And the idea he had was to establish a place of work where engineers"},{"time":809000,"text":"can feel the joy of technological innovation,"},{"time":813000,"text":"be aware of their mission to society and work to their heart's content."},{"time":818000,"text":"I couldn't improve on this as a good example"},{"time":822000,"text":"of how flow enters the workplace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"Now, when we do studies --"},{"time":828000,"text":"we have, with other colleagues around the world,"},{"time":832000,"text":"done over 8,000 interviews of people -- from Dominican monks,"},{"time":837000,"text":"to blind nuns, to Himalayan climbers, to Navajo shepherds --"},{"time":844000,"text":"who enjoy their work."},{"time":846000,"text":"And regardless of the culture,"},{"time":848000,"text":"regardless of education or whatever, there are these seven conditions"},{"time":855000,"text":"that seem to be there when a person is in flow."},{"time":859000,"text":"There's this focus that, once it becomes intense,"},{"time":863000,"text":"leads to a sense of ecstasy, a sense of clarity:"},{"time":867000,"text":"you know exactly what you want to do from one moment to the other;"},{"time":870000,"text":"you get immediate feedback."},{"time":872000,"text":"You know that what you need to do"},{"time":874000,"text":"is possible to do, even though difficult,"},{"time":877000,"text":"and sense of time disappears, you forget yourself,"},{"time":880000,"text":"you feel part of something larger."},{"time":883000,"text":"And once the conditions are present,"},{"time":886000,"text":"what you are doing becomes worth doing for its own sake."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891000,"text":"In our studies, we represent the everyday life of people in this simple scheme."},{"time":897000,"text":"And we can measure this very precisely, actually,"},{"time":901000,"text":"because we give people electronic pagers that go off 10 times a day,"},{"time":905000,"text":"and whenever they go off you say what you're doing, how you feel,"},{"time":910000,"text":"where you are, what you're thinking about."},{"time":912000,"text":"And two things that we measure is the amount of challenge"},{"time":915000,"text":"people experience at that moment and the amount of skill"},{"time":919000,"text":"that they feel they have at that moment."},{"time":922000,"text":"So for each person we can establish an average,"},{"time":925000,"text":"which is the center of the diagram."},{"time":928000,"text":"That would be your mean level of challenge and skill,"},{"time":931000,"text":"which will be different from that of anybody else."},{"time":934000,"text":"But you have a kind of a set point there, which would be in the middle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939000,"text":"If we know what that set point is,"},{"time":941000,"text":"we can predict fairly accurately when you will be in flow,"},{"time":946000,"text":"and it will be when your challenges are higher than average"},{"time":949000,"text":"and skills are higher than average."},{"time":951000,"text":"And you may be doing things very differently from other people,"},{"time":955000,"text":"but for everyone that flow channel, that area there,"},{"time":959000,"text":"will be when you are doing what you really like to do --"},{"time":963000,"text":"play the piano, be with your best friend, perhaps work,"},{"time":969000,"text":"if work is what provides flow for you."},{"time":973000,"text":"And then the other areas become less and less positive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":977000,"text":"Arousal is still good because you are over-challenged there."},{"time":982000,"text":"Your skills are not quite as high as they should be,"},{"time":984000,"text":"but you can move into flow fairly easily"},{"time":987000,"text":"by just developing a little more skill."},{"time":990000,"text":"So, arousal is the area where most people learn from,"},{"time":994000,"text":"because that's where they're pushed beyond their comfort zone"},{"time":1000000,"text":"and to enter that -- going back to flow --"},{"time":1003000,"text":"then they develop higher skills."},{"time":1005000,"text":"Control is also a good place to be,"},{"time":1009000,"text":"because there you feel comfortable, but not very excited."},{"time":1013000,"text":"It's not very challenging any more."},{"time":1016000,"text":"And if you want to enter flow from control,"},{"time":1018000,"text":"you have to increase the challenges."},{"time":1021000,"text":"So those two are ideal and complementary areas"},{"time":1025000,"text":"from which flow is easy to go into."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1029000,"text":"The other combinations of challenge and skill"},{"time":1032000,"text":"become progressively less optimal."},{"time":1035000,"text":"Relaxation is fine -- you still feel OK."},{"time":1037000,"text":"Boredom begins to be very aversive"},{"time":1042000,"text":"and apathy becomes very negative:"},{"time":1046000,"text":"you don't feel that you're doing anything,"},{"time":1050000,"text":"you don't use your skills, there's no challenge."},{"time":1052000,"text":"Unfortunately, a lot of people's experience is in apathy."},{"time":1057000,"text":"The largest single contributor to that experience"},{"time":1064000,"text":"is watching television; the next one is being in the bathroom, sitting."},{"time":1070000,"text":"Even though sometimes watching television"},{"time":1076000,"text":"about seven to eight percent of the time is in flow,"},{"time":1080000,"text":"but that's when you choose a program you really want to watch"},{"time":1083000,"text":"and you get feedback from it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1086000,"text":"So the question we are trying to address -- and I'm way over time --"},{"time":1092000,"text":"is how to put more and more of everyday life in that flow channel."},{"time":1098000,"text":"And that is the kind of challenge that we're trying to understand."},{"time":1103000,"text":"And some of you obviously know how to do that spontaneously"},{"time":1106000,"text":"without any advice, but unfortunately a lot of people don't."},{"time":1110000,"text":"And that's what our mandate is, in a way, to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1116000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1117000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}